****************************************************************************************************
* The Account Management App        
* @author dbernstein@duraspace.org
****************************************************************************************************

To run execute  mvn jetty:run and open http://localhost:8080/ama in your browser.
To use an alternate port use -Djetty.port option.

If you wish to run the unit tests (which include the selenium browser tests as well) you must specify
the jetty port 9000 as in: 

mvn -Djetty.port=9000 clean install;

##Note:  I tried to parameterize the webapp host:port using the System.getProperty("jetty.port", "8080") method
##		 to no avail - so for the time being the integration test url entry point is hardcoded to localhost:9000.
## --dbernstein


You might need to install the following packages if you want the selenium tests to work:

sudo apt-get install firefox 
sudo apt-get install xvfb
sudo apt-get install xauth
sudo apt-get install xfonts-base


****************************************************************************************************
* Eclipse Users
****************************************************************************************************
To generate project and classpath files for eclipse, simply run the following from the project root:

mvn eclipse:eclipse -DdownloadSources=true -DdownloadJavadocs=true
